          "Zinc displaces Copper from Copper Sulfate solution."
        ],
        "whyItMatters": "It tells us how to extract metals and which ones will corrode easily.",
        "terminology": [
          "Displacement",
          "Reactivity"
        ],
        "detailedExplanation": "If you put a more reactive metal into a solution of a less reactive metal's salt, the more reactive metal kicks the less reactive one out.",
        "observedIn": [
          "Rusting of iron",
          "Color change in solutions"
        ],
        "visualSupport": [
          "Diagram of Iron nail turning brown in blue Copper Sulfate solution."
        ],
        "visualAssets": [],
        "importantNotes": [
          "Always check the order before writing a reaction equation."
        ],
        "memoryTechniques": [
          "KING SNAKE: K, Na, Ca, Mg, Al, Zn, Fe, Pb, H, Cu, Ag, Au"
        ],
        "conceptSummary": [
          "Metals are ordered by reactivity; higher metals displace lower ones."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "definitions": [
      {
        "term": "Displacement Reaction",
        "definition": "A reaction where a more reactive element replaces a less reactive element from its compound."
      },
      {
        "term": "Reactivity Series",
        "definition": "The arrangement of metals in decreasing order of their reactivity."
      }
    ],
    "workedExamples": [
      {
        "title": "Predicting Reaction: Iron + Copper Sulfate",
        "problem": "Will Iron react with Copper Sulfate? Write the equation.",
        "diagramRef": "reactivity-ladder",
        "given": [
          "Metal: Iron (Fe)",
          "Salt: Copper Sulfate (CuSO4)"
        ],
        "formula": [
          "Fe + CuSO4 -> ?"
        ],
        "steps": [
          "Check positions: Fe is above Cu.",
          "Reaction occurs."
        ],
        "solutionSteps": [
          "Write formula: Fe + CuSO4",
          "Substitute: FeSO4 + Cu",
          "Balance: Already balanced."
        ],
        "reasoning": [
          "Iron is more reactive than Copper, so it displaces it."
        ],
        "explanation": "The blue color of the solution fades as Copper is removed and Iron Sulfate (green) forms.",
        "finalAnswer": "Fe + CuSO4 -> FeSO4 + Cu",
        "latex": "Fe + CuSO_4 \\rightarrow FeSO_4 + Cu",
        "displayLatex": "\\text{Fe} + \\text{CuSO}_4 \\rightarrow \\text{FeSO}_4 + \\text{Cu}"
      }
    ],
    "revisionSection": {
      "definitions": [
        "Reactivity Series: Order of metals by reactivity."
      ],
      "formulas": [
        "A + BC -> AC + B (if A > B)"
      ],
      "facts": [
        "Gold and Platinum are found in free state.",
        "Sodium is stored in kerosene."
      ],
      "keywords": [
        "Displacement",
        "Oxidation"
